"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>Are you taking on the crinkle swimsuit trend?为什么或者为什么不？加入下面的对话。</em> </p></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4> MORE IN WOMEN&#39;S FASHION</h4><ul class="articleList"><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/would-you-share-clothes-with-your-mother-this-mom-68-and-daughter-31-gave-it-a-try-dc6516d1?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Would You Share Clothes With Your Mother? This Mom, 68, and Daughter, 31, Gave It a Try</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/younger-clients-worse-manners-how-luxury-shopping-has-changed-since-1976-e8fcda7d?mod=article_relatedinline&amp;mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Younger Clients, Worse Manners: How Luxury Shopping Has Changed Over 50 Years</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/your-generation-invented-these-looks-gen-z-doesnt-care-504fa4fa?mod=article_relatedinline&amp;mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Your Generation Invented These Looks. Gen Z Doesn&#39;t Care.</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/what-is-gen-x-style-c77ac55f?mod=article_relatedinline&amp;mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Does Gen X Have No Style?</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sandals-in-the-city-be65950b?mod=article_relatedinline&amp;mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">City Streets Are Gross, but You Can Still Wear Sandals—if You Choose Them Carefully</a></li></ul></div></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/they-smooth-out-every-curve-why-popcorn-swimsuits-are-everywhere-this-summer-bc5ecc5b</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/they-smooth-out-every-curve-why-popcorn-swimsuits-are-everywhere-this-summer-bc5ecc5b<category> off duty</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[In Europe, Far Right is Gaining Influence. Spain Could Be Next.]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Economic angst, an unsolved refugee crisis and the war in Ukraine are boosting far-right nationalists and putting centrists on the defensive <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819850/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="Vox leader Santiago Abascal speaks during an election campaign event in Zaragoza, Spain." referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> Vox leader Santiago Abascal speaks during an election campaign event in Zaragoza, Spain. Marcos Cebrián/Contacto/Zuma Press <span>Marcos Cebrián/Contacto/Zuma Press</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001065967"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001065967"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/margherita-stancati" itemprop="url" rel="author">Margherita Stancati</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 20, 2023 5:30 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/far-right-looks-to-seize-on-spanish-election-919439b4"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> VALENCIA, Spain—For decades after the death of dictator Francisco Franco, Spain was viewed as largely immune to the appeal of the far right. That is no longer so. After years in opposition, the far-right <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/old-fashioned-conservatism-stirs-in-spain-free-market-popular-party-vox-c3dca915?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Vox party has emerged as a likely kingmaker</a> in Spain&#39;s coming parliamentary elections.</p><p> Across Western Europe, stridently nationalist parties considered fringe just a few years ago are moving to the center stage, promising to banish crime, restore traditional values, increase welfare and disempower what they describe as out-of-touch elites.</p><p> The groups are gaining popularity over the failure of governments to address the economic woes of the working class and solve a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/europe-tries-to-bridge-its-migration-divide-c8b1707c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">slow-burn refugee crisis</a> . In some countries, they are also benefiting from growing fatigue over Europe&#39;s continued support for Ukraine against Russia&#39;s invasion.</p><p> “A right-wing populist backlash by the white working class was inevitable,” said Thomas Greven, a professor of political science at the Free University of Berlin who studies right-wing populism in Europe and America. “对我来说，这可以追溯到中左翼社会民主党未能以社会可接受的方式管理日益激烈的全球竞争。”</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>What can be done about the rise of far-right nationalism in Europe?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> Spain is shaping up to become the next example of the trend. The moderately conservative Popular Party is leading in the polls ahead of Sunday&#39;s election, but it is unlikely to secure the votes it needs to rule alone.</p><p> That is why its leadership is reluctantly considering an alliance with Vox, a party that prominent members of the PP have described as extremist, xenophobic and hostile to women.</p><p> The radical right “is becoming normalized,” said Rafael Bardají, a political strategist for Vox. “一旦有了像梅洛尼（意大利）这样的政府，人们看到你时就不再闻到硫磺味了。”</p><p> The trend is evident across the continent. In Italy, Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni is leading Western Europe&#39;s <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/italy-strips-some-gay-couples-of-parental-recognition-4f3993c1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">most right-wing government in decades</a> . In Scandinavia, the Sweden Democrats are providing <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/far-right-party-in-sweden-drives-opposition-bloc-to-election-win-11663185814?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">vital outside support</a> to the ruling coalition in Stockholm. In France, the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/marine-le-pen-wants-france-to-chart-its-own-course-between-u-s-and-russia-11665753470?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">popularity of the far-right candidate</a> Marine Le Pen is growing and the gap in opinion polls between her and President Emmanuel Macron has narrowed.</p><p> Elsewhere, centrist parties are struggling to isolate <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/germany-labels-part-of-nativist-opposition-party-an-extreme-right-group-11584038861?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">groups long shunned as pariahs</a> .在德国，本土主义选择党（AfD），即德国另类选择党，最近赢得了第一次地区选举。 Its popularity is close to a record high, making it the country&#39;s second-most popular party, according to polls. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819861?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Popular Party leader Alberto Núñez Feijó.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: pau barrena/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819128?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Spain&#39;s Prime Minister Pedro Sánchez.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Paul Hanna/Bloomberg</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> While the messages of Europe&#39;s far-right parties vary across the continent, their popularity is generally driven by mainly white, Christian lower-middle- and working-class voters <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/europeans-poorer-inflation-economy-255eb629?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">who feel economically left behind</a> and oppose social change.</p><p> The parties&#39; focus on upholding the interests of the native-born and their resistance against rising diversity in society marks them apart from established conservative forces, political scientists say. So do their admiration for foreign strongman leaders and their authoritarian tendencies expressed in their disdain for institutions like the courts or the free press, which they regard as biased and left-leaning. <strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p> Increasingly, far-right parties have been focusing on culture-war issues, such as gender identity and climate change.</p><p> Even where they don&#39;t win elections, the far right is pulling mainstream parties away from the center and influencing how their countries are run.他们日益突出的地位可能会重塑非洲大陆在移民、气候和 LGBTQ 群体权利等问题上的政治格局。</p><p> Mainstream conservatives increasingly find themselves in the predicament of having to decide whether to join hands with their more right-wing competitors, co-opt their ideas or risk staying out of power.</p><p> The outcome of the Spanish election is hard to predict.它们仍有可能为现任社会党总理佩德罗·桑切斯带来新的任期。</p><p> But polls show the PP is widely expected to fare better, with around 35% of Spaniards planning to vote for it, according to the latest polls. Vox is expected to win 13% of the vote, roughly in line with the previous election. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="841" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819103?width=1260&amp;height=841" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A Vox poster shows cards with symbols representing feminism, communism, the LGBTQ community, the squatters movement and the Catalan independence flag being dropped into a trash can.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: VIOLETA SANTOS MOURA/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Alberto Núñez Feijóo, the PP&#39;s leader and front-runner to be Spain&#39;s next prime minister, has said he doesn&#39;t want to share power with Vox, whose supporters and members include admirers of Franco, the late Spanish dictator. But the PP&#39;s best shot at winning an absolute majority in parliament is by doing just that.</p><p> Following elections in the coastal region of Valencia in May, the two parties quickly reached a power-sharing agreement to replace the center-left administration in one of the richest and most populated parts of Spain.</p><p> For Vox, it was a coup.直到几个月前，它还是西班牙联邦政治体系中的边缘参与者。 Vox 只在西班牙 17 个地区之一卡斯蒂利亚和莱昂的地方政府任职。在一些地区议会中，Vox 政客没有一个席位。现在他们在西班牙所有地区的议会中都有席位，并在其中四个地区与人民党分享权力。更多可能会随之而来。</p><p> “We are very used to being in the margins,” said Carlos Flores, a prominent Vox politician in Valencia. “Being in government in Valencia, in other communities and possibly at the national level is an enormous leap for us.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819109?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A Vox rally in Barcelona was greeted by protesters.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Kike Rincon/Contacto/Zuma Press </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819056?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The PP&#39;s María Guardiola shakes hands with Vox&#39;s Angel Pelayo Gordill after signing a deal to jointly rule the Spanish region of Extremadura.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Jorge Armestar/Contacto/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Like other radical right politicians, Flores is an admirer of Hungary&#39;s populist Prime Minister Viktor Orbán, whose government the European Union&#39;s parliament has called an “electoral autocracy” for hounding the free press, eroding the independence of courts, and criminalizing the work of certain NGOs.</p><p> Vox was founded a decade ago by ex-PP members who felt their party was moving too close to the center. 2017 年加泰罗尼亚分离主义者举行非法公投，要求该地区独立后，该节目受到欢迎。Vox 指责政府对分离主义者过于软弱。 Two years later, it won its first seats in Spain&#39;s parliament.</p><p> “These are disgruntled conservative voters who felt their party failed them.真正推动他们前进的是西班牙的团结受到威胁，”马德里智库埃尔卡诺皇家研究所所长查尔斯·鲍威尔说。 Vox 还讨论了文化战争问题。 “They are reacting against what they see as an attack against Spanish values: national identity, Catholicism, even bullfighting.”</p><p> Among those who plan to vote for Vox on Sunday is Carmen Ramirez, 63. The party&#39;s opposition to regional autonomy is a key reason she supports it.</p><p> “Vox has values that are completely in line with mine: the importance of Spanish unity, the respect for traditions and religions,” said Ramirez, who works for a women&#39;s clothing business.她并不反对移民，但表示应该根据 Vox 的政策加强对移民的监管。</p><p> Vox is pushing for a naval blockade to stop <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/greece-migrant-ship-reveals-perilous-route-to-europe-260dd49b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">migrants crossing the Mediterranean on small boats</a> . It also wants migrants who enter Spain illegally to be immediately expelled.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> In Valencia, Vox will oversee departments including culture, agriculture and justice. Vox 政界人士表示，这种模式可以为在国家层面与人民党分享权力提供蓝图。</p><p> For many PP voters and party members, an alliance with Vox is hard to swallow. 5月地区选举后，埃斯特雷马杜拉南部地区的人民党领导人表示，她永远不会与Vox组建联盟。 She singled out the party&#39;s dismissal of gender as a contributing factor in violence against women, its “dehumanizing” rhetoric on migrants, and a recent campaign poster that showed a hand throwing the rainbow symbol of the LGBTQ community into a trash can.</p><p> Days later, under pressure from her party leadership, she made a U-turn and struck a deal with Vox to jointly rule the region.</p><p> What impact being in government could have on fringe parties such as Vox is an open question. In Italy, Meloni&#39;s party has become more establishment-friendly since it became the country&#39;s most popular party.</p><p> Brothers of Italy, which evolved from what was left of the Fascist Party after World War II, has taken up mainstream positions on questions such as the EU and Russia&#39;s war in Ukraine.</p><p> Meloni remains <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/italy-strips-some-gay-couples-of-parental-recognition-4f3993c1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">more radical on social issues</a> , such as immigration and the parental rights of gay and lesbian couples. Her government has made it <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/deadly-shipwreck-shakes-italys-anti-immigration-government-b35a6d81?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">harder for private boats to rescue migrants</a> in the Mediterranean.</p><p> Last week, she addressed a Vox campaign rally in Valencia via video link and endorsed the party&#39;s leader, Santiago Abascal.</p><p> “Dear friends,” Meloni said. “The time of patriots has arrived.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819154?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Giorgia Meloni addressing a rally in Valencia.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Jorge Gil/Contacto/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> <em>—José Bautista contributed to this article</em> .</p><p> Write to Margherita Stancati at <a href="mailto:margherita.stancati@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">margherita.stancati@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/far-right-looks-to-seize-on-spanish-election-919439b4</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/far-right-looks-to-seize-on-spanish-election-919439b4<author><![CDATA[Margherita Stancati]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>Human Migration</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>选举</category><category>国家/总统选举</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Pedro Sánchez</category><category> Santiago Abascal</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>human migration</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>选举</category><category>总统选举</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Pivotal Mission in Ukraine’s Counteroffensive: Hunting for Mines]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>事实证明，地雷是基辅缓慢反攻的最大挑战之一<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819475/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="乌克兰南部新瓦西利夫卡附近，一名乌克兰军人在用作临时基地的房屋内组装金属探测器。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>乌克兰南部新瓦西利夫卡附近，一名乌克兰军人在用作临时基地的房屋内组装金属探测器。 <span></span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001065730"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001065730"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/isabel-coles" itemprop="url" rel="author">Isabel Coles</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name">Ievgeniia Sivorka Emanuele Satolli 为《华尔街日报》拍摄的照片</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 20 日上午 12:05（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-pivotal-mission-in-ukraines-counteroffensive-hunting-for-mines-78197558"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>乌克兰巴哈蒂尔——乌克兰士兵在漆黑中出发，偷偷穿过炮弹坑坑洼洼的田野，执行反攻中最重要的任务之一，也是最危险的任务之一。</p><p>战斗工程师（被称为工兵）配备金属探测器、铲子和抓钩， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-adopts-slow-approach-to-counteroffensive-our-problem-everywhere-is-the-sky-a2e51d7a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与俄罗斯军队一起沿着前线</a>寻找地雷，同时努力不被附近敌人发现。</p><p> “你不能紧张，”一位呼号为“渔夫”的 49 岁工兵说道，他领导着乌克兰第 68 猎兵旅的 50 人小组。</p><p>六月初，乌克兰军队使用西方捐赠的坦克和其他装甲车进行的初步推进在俄罗斯雷区沉没，之后乌克兰军队求助于费舍曼这样的人来扫清前进的道路。</p><p>在西方军队训练和装备基辅部队发动进攻的几个月里，俄罗斯建造了一些自世界大战以来最广泛的战场防御工事。乌克兰总统泽伦斯基哀叹西方盟友行动不够迅速，让俄罗斯有时间在比加州还大的地区布雷。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819477?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> “你不能紧张，”49 岁的工兵费舍曼说。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>尽管面临挑战，乌克兰<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-war-counteroffensive-frontlines-russia-add3e4e4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">自六周多前开始反攻以来</a>夺回的领土比俄罗斯在相同个月内夺取的领土还要多。基辅尚未将其所有部队投入战斗，保留了一些受过西方训练的部队来利用俄罗斯防御的任何突破口。</p><p>但进展速度比乌克兰和西方官员所希望的要慢，俄罗斯的主要防线仍然在前面——布满反坦克和杀伤人员地雷的田野、混凝土加固的战壕、铁丝网、龙牙和反坦克沟渠。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>总部位于英国的皇家联合军种研究所智囊团在今年早些时候的一份报告中表示，工程已被证明是俄罗斯军队最强大的部门之一。包括地雷在内的障碍物旨在减缓乌克兰军队的速度，并将前进的步兵引导到俄罗斯攻击直升机、火炮和无人机可以拦截的位置。</p><p>一名乌克兰军官获得的一份 2023 年俄罗斯手册规定了使用地雷挫败乌克兰机械化纵队的指导方针。一些反坦克地雷将不加伪装地埋设，以将乌克兰军队转移到埋有隐藏地雷的地区。其他的则应在障碍物（例如故障车辆和被毁坏的道路）旁边成群种植，以诱捕试图绕过它们的乌克兰军队。</p><p>去年美国向乌克兰提供的价值6000万美元的军事援助中就包括扫雷设备。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          edgetoedge
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/09e46d1a-2d98-4a70-8257-bf1ff52a084c.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>其中的解决方案包括扫雷线装药，它会在雷区发射一枚装有炸药线的小型火箭，并引爆附近的任何地雷。乌克兰已经拥有苏联开发的同类产品。</p><p>据跟踪双方在战争中损失的独立分析小组 Oryx 称，芬兰向乌克兰提供的六辆 Leopard 2R 装甲扫雷车中的一辆在反攻初期被摧毁，两辆被损坏。</p><p>渔夫手机上的卫星图像显示了乌克兰军队所面临的情况：它显示了俄罗斯阵地前的五排反坦克地雷带。但在清理敌人的地雷之前，工兵必须在自己的地雷中打开一个缺口。</p><p>渔夫是一位狂热的钓鱼爱好者，他将自己的爱好与工作进行了比较，因为两者都涉及放置诱饵和等待捕获。他在 2015 年冲突的早期阶段与俄罗斯作战，但在去年全面入侵之前，他又回到建筑行业工作。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="2050" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/96ff07b0-8f9b-4a93-a4a1-8eac8dac9fcb-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>去年抵达武勒达尔附近的前线后，他的手下（自称“渔民”）开始在大约曼哈顿四分之一面积的区域埋设约 25,000 枚地雷。有时需要携带多枚反坦克地雷跋涉数英里，每枚重 22 磅。</p><p>渔民们埋下的地雷炸毁了俄罗斯第 155 海军步兵旅，在一次失败的冬季攻势中挫败了对武勒达尔村周围的多次袭击。渔夫手机上的一段视频显示，三辆毫无防备的俄罗斯坦克沿着雪原上刻出的轨道排成一列前进。费舍曼说，敌方工兵此前已经清理了道路，但他的人在夜色掩护下再次布雷。视频显示，第一辆坦克滚过地雷，引发爆炸，促使车队的其他车辆掉头。</p><p>随着攻势迫在眉睫，渔民的任务是在不透露乌克兰军队打算攻击的地点的情况下，清理出一条穿过自己防御工事的道路。为了让敌人猜不透，工兵们从他们埋设的地雷中取出炸药，同时留下外壳作为诱饵。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819482?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">所谓的渔民的任务是在前线寻找地雷。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819481?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">一名工兵展示他如何探测并清除地面上的地雷。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>乌克兰军队在渔民前线取得了一些早期战术胜利，夺回了东部村庄布拉霍达特内。但是，和其他地方一样，地雷已被证明是一个大问题。有一次，乌克兰军队占领了俄罗斯阵地，却遭到猛烈炮火攻击。一名留着山羊胡、呼号为“布巴”的工兵说，他们在试图带着伤员撤退时触发了杀伤人员地雷。</p><p> “当我们进入被占领土时，我们是盲目的，”布巴说。</p><p>工兵们戴着夜视镜，用金属探测器扫描前方的地面。有时，他们距离俄罗斯阵地如此之近，以至于可以听到敌人的声音。当金属探测器收到信号时，它们会探测地球以确定地下有什么。没有紧张的余地。 “你的手不能颤抖，”渔夫说道，他穿着一件印有“晚上好，我们来自乌克兰”的 T 恤。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="922" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/02c9bc6f-0429-45df-9c7f-077f6a8a6db3-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>检测到的金属通常是无害的弹片，散落在乌克兰南部前线沿线的田野上。但如果是地雷，工兵们会用短柄铲子将其揭开，然后用绳子系上抓钩。</p><p>他们在安全距离外拉动绳索，以拆除反坦克地雷。俄罗斯军队经常在其下方埋设杀伤人员地雷，当反坦克地雷被拆除时就会触发。 “风险总是存在的，”布巴说。</p><p>绊网在黑暗中是看不见的，因此工兵有时会等到黎明才出去寻找它们。费舍曼说，为此，最好的工具是簧片：拉紧但屈服强度足以不会触发绊线。 “没有人想出比这更好的工具，”他一边说，一边从流经的河岸上拔下一根芦苇。这些人当时正在执行前线任务，暂时休息，住在一间空房子里，等待进一步的命令。</p><p>费舍曼说，工兵的预期寿命很短。尽管如此，他说到目前为止他还没有因地雷而丧生。他认为这是他最大的成就。</p><p> “我来这里不是为了成为英雄，”他说。 “我来这里只是为了完成我的工作：赢得战争。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819480?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">工兵在前往另一个地点之前准备并打包他们的设备。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819474?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">渔夫说，没有在地雷中失去一个人是他最大的成就。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>写信给 Isabel Coles，邮箱为<a href="mailto:isabel.coles@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">isabel.coles@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 04:05:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-pivotal-mission-in-ukraines-counteroffective-hunting-for-mines-78197558</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-pivotal-mission-in-ukraines-counteroffective-hunting-for-mines-78197558<author><![CDATA[Isabel Coles]]></author><category> gfx-contrib</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>华尔街日报</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Political Rise of Ultra-Orthodox Jews Shakes Israel’s Sense of Identity]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>快速增长的宗教保守派团体与内塔尼亚胡结盟，挑战最高法院，引发大规模抗议运动；义务兵役制成为一个关键问题<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816908/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="布内布拉克 (Bnei Brak) 聚集了大量极端正统的犹太人，被称为正统派 (Haredim)。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>布内布拉克 (Bnei Brak) 聚集了大量极端正统的犹太人，被称为正统派 (Haredim)。 <span></span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001067629"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001067629"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者：多夫<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dov-lieber" itemprop="url" rel="author">·利伯 (Dov Lieber)</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/shayndi-raice" itemprop="url" rel="author">Shayndi Raice</a></span>科比·沃尔夫 (Kobi Wolf) 为《华尔街日报》拍摄的照片</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 20 日上午 12:01 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israel-ultra-orthodox-haredim-military-service-supreme-court-of-ultra-orthodox-jews-shakes-israels-sense-of-identity-b3155e01"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>以色列伯内布拉克——自以色列建国以来，犹太以色列人的义务兵役被广泛接受为分裂社会中的团结力量。</p><p>现在这个问题有可能导致国家分裂。以色列的极端正统犹太人是一个快速发展且强大的政治集团，长期以来一直回避服兵役以及世俗社会的其他方面。他们<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/in-israel-army-service-is-required-for-all-that-could-now-change-2c76624d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">争取永久免役的努力</a>多次被以色列最高法院挫败。他们与总理本杰明·内塔尼亚胡领导的利库德集团结盟，推动<a href="https://www.wsj.com/story/why-israelis-are-protesting-netanyahu-governments-judicial-overhaul-0933acc5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">司法改革，以削弱法院的力量</a>。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israel-protests-flare-up-in-new-push-to-stop-judicial-overhaul-9f939aac?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">改革的第一部分引发了大规模抗议活动，连续 28 周震撼以色列</a>，预计最早将于周日获得以色列议会批准。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=D894069B-A5EE-4723-95BE-F7213DF5ACA0&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fisrael-ultra-orthodox-haredim-military-service-supreme-court-of-ultra-orthodox-jews-shakes-israels-sense-of-identity-b3155e01&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu spoke with Wall Street Journal reporter Dov Lieber about the country&#39;s Ultra-Orthodox in response to their increasing political power in Israel. Photo: Dror Lebendiger for the Wall Street Journal<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>这场冲突触及以色列固有身份问题的核心：它是现代自由民主国家还是由宗教定义的社会？许多世俗的以色列人将司法改革视为增强那些利用宗教来削弱基本公民权利的人的权力的一步。</p><p> “世俗社会想要一个完整的现代国家，”耶路撒冷智库以色列民主研究所的学者吉拉德·马拉赫说。 “极端正统派的目标是建立一个强大的宗教社会。”</p><p>极端正统的犹太人，如叶霍舒亚·梅努钦 (Yehoshua Menuchin)，40 岁了，有妻子、六个儿子，没有稳定的工作，他称自己为正统派，意思是那些在上帝面前颤抖的人。许多正统派男人不定期工作，而是选择在称为犹太学校的宗教神学院学习神圣文本。他们认为，他们通过保留犹太传统并为以色列提供神圣保护，以自己的方式为国家做出贡献。</p><p> “我认为我们做出的牺牲丝毫不减，”梅努钦说。 “我已经传承了这个世界的乐趣。我已经放弃了餐馆、电影院、俱乐部。我一生中已经放弃了很多东西。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816909?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">布内布拉克 (Bnei Brak) 的一所犹太学校，男人们在那里领取津贴来学习宗教文献。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>以色列社会的一个元素梅努钦和许多其他正统派人士都回避的是义务兵役，这是以色列主流社会的一种成人仪式。大多数犹太男女从 18 岁开始都会在军队服役两到三年。在军队中建立的友谊也可以作为军旅生活后职业联系的基础。</p><p>以色列最高法院曾两次否决旨在正式将正统派排除在征兵之外的立法，最近一次是在 2017 年，理由是该立法造成了公民的不平等待遇。法院已允许临时豁免，以便政府找到解决方案。</p><p>这些决定加剧了宗教保守派与最高法院之间的摩擦，最高法院<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-judge-at-the-heart-of-israels-constitutional-crisis-de698670?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">长期以来一直是个人自由的坚定捍卫者</a>，维护以色列阿拉伯公民、妇女和 LGBTQ 群体的权利。</p><p>正统派现在拥有反击的政治影响力。他们的两个政党——一个代表欧洲血统的犹太人，另一个代表来自大中东的犹太人——组成了现任政府中仅次于利库德集团的第二大集团，在议会 120 个席位中拥有 18 个席位。他们是内塔尼亚胡掌控权力的关键，因为他的联盟总共只控制 64 个席位。他们经常威胁说，如果他们的各种要求得不到满足，他们就会离开联盟。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="841" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816911?width=1260&amp;height=841" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">犹太东正教团体在 Ponevezh Yeshiva 学习。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="841" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816912?width=1260&amp;height=841" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">议会中的正统派希望颁布立法，允许在某些公共场所将男女分开。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/video/series/in-depth-features/wsj-exclusive-an-interview-with-israeli-prime-minister-benjamin-netanyahu/D95FB00D-DFCE-4B6E-9B89-889EB0968CE4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在接受《华尔街日报》采访时</a>，内塔尼亚胡称最高法院是“地球上最积极的司法法院”，并表示“以色列公众越来越认识到司法改革的必要性。”不过，他表示，他的目标是缓和一些最初的提议，而是“以谨慎的方式推进”。</p><p>政府希望彻底改革这一制度，并将更多权力交给民选官员。提案包括削弱法院推翻政府决定的能力，并赋予立法者在挑选新法官的委员会中的多数发言权。</p><p>来自世俗以色列人和一些温和宗教犹太人的强烈反对。</p><p> 3 月，51 岁的预备役中校罗恩·谢尔夫 (Ron Scherf) 帮助<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israeli-judicial-overhaul-pits-secular-religious-communities-against-each-other-a4177c16?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">组织了一次穿过以色列最大的正统派城市布内布拉克 (Bnei Brak) 的游行</a>。抗议者举着标语，敦促正统派参军。一些正统派向抗议者投掷传单，称他们永远不会在“叛教”军队中服役。”</p><p> “我们确实相信以色列的世俗和正统派之间需要签订新的合同，”舍夫说。 “如果目前的情况不改变，我认为以色列不可能作为一个自由、繁荣和强大的国家存在。”</p><p> “我们即将发生一场重大冲突，”受欢迎的正统派媒体人物伊斯雷尔·科恩反驳道。 “如果没有一方承担责任，事情的结局就不会好。” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="1038" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/a57e9a71-225e-434e-b047-fcb1a5e45e4e-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>除了服兵役之外，许多以色列人认为正统的生活方式对该国未来的繁荣构成了直接威胁。大约一半的正统派男人不工作。相反，他们从事宗教研究，靠妻子的工资、慈善机构、政府补助和补贴生活。根据以色列中央统计局的数据，随着出生率稳步上升，目前每名女性生育 6.5 个孩子左右，而普通人口的生育率约为 3.0 个，据以色列中央统计局称，大约 130 万正统派占总人口的 13.3%。作为增长最快的群体，到 2065 年，他们将占以色列总人口的近三分之一。</p><p>正统派利用他们的政治权力扩大市政税收折扣、早期儿童保育补贴以及对低收入大家庭的租金援助——从技术上讲，所有以色列人都可以获得这些福利，但由于其人口特征，这些福利往往有利于正统派。据以色列民主研究所称，他们或他们的犹太学院还为约 14 万名全日制学习的正统男子提供津贴或助学金。该研究所由一位前中间派政治家领导，发现正统派家庭缴纳的税款比非正统派家庭少三分之一。</p><p>在 5 月份写给内塔尼亚胡的一封信中，超过 200 名以色列主要经济学家警告说， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israels-netanyahu-faces-pushback-over-plan-to-subsidize-ultra-orthodox-schools-45568a14?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">一项计划增加对拒绝教授世俗科目的正统教育机构的资助</a>，同时增加全日制托拉学习者的津贴，将使以色列转变为“ “第三世界”经济让正统儿童无法为今天的劳动力做好准备。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="841" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816913?width=1260&amp;height=841" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Ponevezh Yeshiva 的外套和帽子。 </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="841" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816916?width=1260&amp;height=841" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">一名男子在布内布拉克的一家旧衣店购物。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israels-judicial-reforms-could-strengthen-religions-role-in-public-life-11674476463?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">正统派的目标是将宗教扩展到公共生活的更多领域</a>。自内塔尼亚胡去年重新掌权以来，他们通过了一项法律，允许医院在犹太节日逾越节期间禁止面包产品进入公立医院。他们还表示，希望颁布立法，允许在某些公共场所或正统派经常参加的活动中将男女分开，以色列律师普遍认为这是违宪的。</p><p>正统派已经在公共生活的许多方面拥有巨大的权力。他们控制着拉巴努特（Rabbanut），这是一个监督婚姻和离婚并决定谁是犹太人的政府机构。拉巴努特长期以来拒绝承认犹太教的任何非正统分支，这一直是一个紧张的问题，特别是在散居国外的犹太人中。他们还对著名的犹太圣地拥有管理控制权。</p><p>最近发生在布内布拉克的抗议活动让耶霍舒亚·梅努钦 (Yehoshua Menuchin) 的妻子德沃拉 (Dvora) 不为所动。 “抗议的人对犹太教一无所知，”她说。 “他们就像婴儿一样。如果他们了解犹太教，他们就不会这样做。”</p><p>她的社区拥挤、喧闹、活泼，行人（包括许多儿童）挤满了狭窄街道的人行道，街道两旁是神圣的书店和小餐馆，出售传统的东欧犹太食品，如 kugel、gefilte 鱼和 cholent。每个角落和每个公交车站旁都矗立着一排排的慈善箱，其中大部分最终将捐给犹太学院的学生及其家人。</p><p>梅努钦一家靠资助约书亚全日制学习的美国捐助者提供的资金、政府补贴、来自朋友或家人的无息贷款以及零工生活。德沃拉大部分时间都呆在家里做饭和打扫卫生，并用一台可以个性化圆顶小帽等犹太物品的机器赚点小钱。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816914?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">行人在 Bnei Brak 过马路。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>梅纽钦在晚上进行宗教主题的讲座。有时他的听众会给他小额捐款。他还花很少的费用修理犹太教，比如护命匣，这是一种小皮盒，里面装有写有《托拉》文字的卷轴，犹太男子在晨祷时将其绑在头上和手臂上。</p><p>梅努钦一家住在一套三居室的公寓里，他们的六个男孩被分在两个房间里。他们所有的家具都是二手买的。</p><p>梅纽钦早上 7 点起得很早，穿着正统派男人穿的黑裤子和白衬衫参加晨祷。早餐后，他开车前往犹太学院，在那里他花了一天的时间主要学习《塔木德》，这是一部古老的犹太文本，是犹太法律的基础。</p><p>梅纽钦的犹太学校——名为 Kisay Rahamim，意为“仁慈之席”，主要服务于北非裔犹太人——要求他用电子卡刷卡进入，这样州政府就可以确认他确实每天都在学习。</p><p>梅努钦和他的孩子们在八年级后停止了所有世俗教育。他们不会读或说英语，而梅努钦只能做基本的加法和减法。他说这就是他度过一生所需要的一切。</p><p>耶路撒冷正统公共事务研究所所长拉比·伊莱·佩利 (Rabbi Eli Paley) 表示，学习托拉的生活方式造就了“好丈夫、好父亲、好社区成员和好志愿者”。</p><p> “那东西不值钱吗？”他说。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816910?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">在 Bnei Brak 的街道上漫步。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>虽然经济学家表示，为犹太学院系统提供资金将使大多数正统派陷入贫困，但他们认为，他们对资本主义的激烈竞争不感兴趣，他们的生活方式让他们感到快乐和满足。</p><p> “如果你去游乐园，或者喝一杯酒，那一刻你会很高兴。但当你学习《托拉》时，快乐就会一直伴随着你，”梅努钦说。</p><p>写信给 Dov Lieber <a href="mailto:dov.lieber@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">（dov.lieber@wsj.com）</a>和 Shayndi Raice（ <a href="mailto:Shayndi.Raice@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Shayndi.Raice@wsj.com</a> ）</p><p id="correction" class="correction"><strong>更正和放大</strong><br>以色列议会（Knesset）有 120 个席位。本文的早期版本错误地称其有 160 个席位。 （7月20日更正）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 04:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/israel-ultra-orthodox-haredim-military-service-supreme-court-of-ultra-orthodox-jews-shakes-israels-sense-of-identity-b3155e01</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/israel-ultra-orthodox-haredim-military-service-supreme-court-of-ultra-orthodox-jews-shakes-israels-sense-of-identity-b3155e01<author><![CDATA[Dov LieberShayndi Raice]]></author><category> gfx-contrib</category><category>摄影委托</category><category>领导者</category><category>华尔街日报</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>宗教</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>religion</category></item></channel></rss>